laboratory_examinations.findings: The infrarenal abdominal aorta is ectatic to 2.0 cm with mural thrombus, resulting in luminal narrowing to 1.4 x 1.0 cm. Severe stenosis in the right common iliac artery (>75%). Complete occlusion of the left common iliac artery. The left superficial femoral artery is somewhat diminutive with intermittent mild-moderate stenosis but remains patent.
